250 g Ground Beef
2 unit(s) Flatbread
3 unit(s) Cream Cheese
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 tsp Smoked Paprika
56 g Spring Mix
113 g Baby Tomatoes
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch strips.
Halve baby tomatoes.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, beef and half the peppers. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add smoked paprika and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a small bowl and carefully wipe the pan clean.

Spread cream cheese onto flatbreads.
Spread beef mixture onto one-half of the flatbreads, then sprinkle mozzarella over top.
Fold the flatbread over onto itself and press firmly to close.
Add stuffed flatbreads to the same pan (from step 2) over medium. (NOTE: Cook in batches for 4 ppl.)
Cook until cheese has melted and flatbreads are golden-brown, 1-2 min per side.

Meanwhile, add tomatoes, remaining peppers, ranch and spring mix to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Divide beef pockets and salad between plates.

If you've opted to get beef, cook beef in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the chorizo.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat before adding smoked paprika.